Info_consent:
INVITATION TO
TAKE PARTIt is time for
us to collect some data so that you can learn how to analyse data using
something that is actually personally relevant to us all. We really appreciate
that the topics we chose are complex and delicate but we hope these questions
will kindle your interest in and critical thinking about the issues relating to gender and sexuality and that, by exploring your responses, we will learn
something interesting together. You are not
obliged to take part in this survey and there will be no consequences to your
assessment on the module whether or not you fill in the form. WHAT WILL I DO?The survey will
take less than five minutes. During the survey, we will ask you some questions
concerning gender and sexuality. WHAT WILL HAPPEN
TO THE RESULTS AND MY PERSONAL INFORMATION?All the
information that you provide will be anonymous. By submitting your
responses, you agree to have your anonymous data analysed by students and staff
on the module for educational purposes. In addition, the anonymous data may
be published in a scientific journal.   CONSENT• I understand
that by indicating my consent below, I am agreeing to take part in the
University of Sussex research described here, and that I have read and
understood this information sheet. • I understand
that my participation is entirely voluntary, that I can choose not to
participate in part or all of the survey, and that I can withdraw at any stage without
having to give a reason and without being penalised in any way. • I understand
that since the survey is anonymous, it will be impossible to withdraw my data
once I have completed and submitted the test.

• I consent to the processing of my personal information for the purposes of
this research. I understand that such information will be treated as
strictly confidential (subject to legal limitations) and handled in accordance
with General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR, 2016).

• I understand that my identity will remain confidential in any written reports
of this research, and that no information I disclose will lead to the
identification in those reports of any individual either by the researchers or
by any other party, without first obtaining my written permission.



If you require
further information, contact Dr Mankin (j.mankin@sussex.ac.uk),
Dr Valášek (M.Valasek@sussex.ac.uk), or Dr Atkinson
(r.atkinson@sussex.ac.uk). If you have any concerns about the way in
which the research has been conducted, contact the Chair of the Science and
Technology Cross-Schools Research Ethics Committee (C-REC), Dr Karen Long
(crecscitec@sussex.ac.uk). The University of Sussex has insurance in place to
cover its legal liabilities in respect of this research. 













































Please indicate
below whether you consent to participate in this research.
Age: How old are you in years?

Debrief_1:
DEBRIEF INFORMATIONThank you very much for taking part in our research!
RESEARCH AIMSWe are hoping to learn more about how people define gender and sexuality.
WHAT WILL HAPPEN TO THE RESULTS AND MY PERSONAL INFORMATION?This data for this research has been collected for the module Analysing data (module code C8891) at the School of Psychology, University of Sussex. As part of the requirements of the module, students will analyse the data during practical classes. In addition, the anonymous data may be published in a scientific journal. 
As previously stated, all data is entirely anonymous and will be held in strict confidentiality. All of your responses thus far have been recorded and saved, so if you are happy for your data to be included in the analysis, you can close this window at any time.
OPTION TO WITHDRAWIf at this point you would like to withdraw your responses for any reason so they are not included in any of the analyses, please enter the word "WITHDRAW" in the text box below and click "Next". We will permanently delete your data before any analysis begins.
If you would like to withdraw, please enter the word "WITHDRAW" in the box below.
